name: Equity
description: Residual interest in assets after deducting all liabilities representing the net worth and ownership capital

name: Expense
description: Outflows or decreases of economic benefits or depletions of assets from delivery of goods or services

name: Liability
description: Financial obligations that reflects money owed to creditors and need to be repaid in the future

name: Off-Balance-Sheet
description: Off-balance sheet accounts, which include commitments, guarantees, and contingencies.

name: Asset
description: Assets or resources with economic value that an individual, corporation or country owns or controls with the expectation that it will provide future benefit

name: Revenue
description: Increases in economic benefits generated from delivery of goods or services before expenses are deducted
